  <title>Overview</title>

  <p><app>HP8970 Companion</app> is a program to enhance and extend the capabilities of the Hewlett Packard 8970 Noise Figure Meter</p>
  <p>The 8970 was built to connect to peripherals <em>(analog pen plotters, or in the case of the 8970B, HPIB pen plotters )</em> that are difficult to obtain thirty years after release or have functions that can be better performed by more modern, cheaper and more capable devices.</p>
  <p>Communicating with noise figure meter over the HPIB, the HP8970 Companion can:</p>
  <list>
  <item><p>Store and upload multiple noise source caliibration tables</p></item>
  <item><p>Command the noise figure meter to sweep whilst accumulating the measured data</p></item>
  <item><p>Plot to the screen the noise vs frequency and gain vs frequency relationship</p></item>
  <item><p>Print the noise and gain plots to a network printer</p></item>
  <item><p>Save the trace data as a CSV file or JSON</p></item>
  <item><p>Recal previously saved JSON format data to re-plot</p></item>
  <item><p>Plot noise and gain vs time for a spot frequency (to see the change over time)</p>
  <item><p>Save the plots in various formats:</p></item>
     <list>
   	<item><p>PNG image</p></item>
        <item><p>PDF page</p></item>
        <item><p>SVG page</p></item>
        <item><p>CSV file</p></item>
        <item><p>JSON file</p></item>
    </list>    
  </item>
</list>

